      "description": "This 1995 Mazda RX-7 FD3S is a superlative example of rotary engineering, maintained to an exacting standard. The 13B-REW sequential twin-turbocharged powerplant delivers linear boost across the rev range, with recent compression tests confirming robust apex seal integrity and factory-spec housing tolerances. The chassis remains taut, utilizing the original double-wishbone suspension geometry and a Torsen limited-slip differential that ensures surgical turn-in and neutral handling. This vehicle retains its factory-spec vacuum routing and cooling system efficiency, free of common heat-soak issues. The undercarriage is pristine, showing no signs of oxidation or structural fatigue. A true collector-grade specimen for the discerning purist.",
